General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 b. Has committed a misdemeanor, and:A misdemeanor, when the person
2 meets at least one of the following criteria:
3 1. Will not be apprehended unless immediately arrested,
4 orarrested.
5 2. May cause physical injury to himself or others, or damage to
6 property unless immediately arrested; orarrested.
7 c. Has committed a A misdemeanor under G.S. 14-72.1, 14-134.3,
8 20-138.1, or 20-138.2; or20-138.2.
9 d. Has committed a A misdemeanor under any of the following statutes:
10 1. G.S. 14-32.5.
11 2. G.S. 14-33(a), 14-33(c)(1), 14-33(c)(2), or 14-34 when the
12 offense was committed by a person with whom the alleged
13 victim has a personal relationship as defined in G.S. 50B-1;
14 orG.S. 50B-1.
15 e. Has committed a A misdemeanor under G.S. 50B-4.1(a);
16 orG.S. 50B-4.1(a).
17 f. Has violated a A pretrial release order entered under G.S. 15A-534 or
18 G.S. 15A-534.1(a)(2).
19 …."
20 SECTION 3. Section 1 of this act becomes effective December 1, 2025, and applies
21 to offenses committed on or after that date. Section 2 of this act is effective when it becomes law
22 and applies to arrests made on or after that date. The remainder of this act is effective when it
23 becomes law.
